00:01:00,042 --> 00:01:04,862
processes such as evaporation,
evapotranspiration, filtration, 

16
00:01:05,062 --> 00:01:09,940
gravity, surface charge attractions,
centrifugal force and pressure.

17
00:01:10,140 --> 00:01:13,540
Gravity is probably the most 
commonly employed method

18
00:01:13,740 --> 00:01:17,815
of liquid solid separation, for the
separation of suspended particles

19
00:01:18,015 --> 00:01:20,249
and bound water. 

20
00:01:20,449 --> 00:01:24,240
Particles that are heavier than 
water set decreasing conditions

21
00:01:24,440 --> 00:01:29,419
at rates based on size of particles,
suspended solids concentrations, 

22
00:01:29,619 --> 00:01:32,128
and flocculation

23
00:01:32,328 --> 00:01:35,928
These are the basic fundamentals
used in the design of settling

24
00:01:36,128 --> 00:01:39,758
thickening tanks in grit and 
sand chambers.

25
00:01:39,958 --> 00:01:43,988
Filtration is also a commonly 
applied mechanism for dewatering.

26
00:01:44,188 --> 00:01:47,976
Many different types of filtration
media are used for water, 

27
00:01:48,176 --> 00:01:52,074
waste water and treated sludge or
biosolids processing.

28
00:01:52,274 --> 00:01:56,263
The most common for the treatment
of fecal sludge are drying beds, 

29
00:01:56,463 --> 00:02:01,463
and planted drying beds. Drying beds
used sand and gravel filter media to

30
00:02:01,663 --> 00:02:05,105
to trap solids on the surface of the
filter bed. While the liquid

31
00:02:05,305 --> 00:02:09,793
percolates through the filter bed
and is collected in a drain or

32
00:02:09,993 --> 00:02:12,136
evaporates. 

33
00:02:12,336 --> 00:02:16,896
Water that can be separated through
gravity or filtration is free water 

34
00:02:17,096 --> 00:02:21,154
that is more easily separated from
solids. This is analogous to water

35
00:02:21,354 --> 00:02:24,898
that can be run out of a towel. If 
you need more liquid removed from

36
00:02:25,098 --> 00:02:29,898
the sludge, then you also need 
drying. For example, by the sun

37
00:02:30,098 --> 00:02:33,991
thorough evaporation under surface
of drying beds. 

38
00:02:34,191 --> 00:02:38,887
Evaporation occurs when water is
released into the air as a vapor.

39
00:02:39,087 --> 00:02:43,970
Transpiration occurs when plants 
release vapor to the air as part of

40
00:02:44,170 --> 00:02:49,212
their metabolic processes. 
