57
00:03:59,743 --> 00:04:04,251
The biodegradable organic matter
in fecal sludge varies depending on

58
00:04:04,451 --> 00:04:10,144
the source. But usually needs to be
stabilized prior to final end use or

59
00:04:10,344 --> 00:04:15,094
disposal. Stabilization involves the
degradation of readily degradable

60
00:04:15,294 --> 00:04:20,164
material, leaving behind more stable
less degradable organics.

61
00:04:20,364 --> 00:04:25,113
This is important in order to reduce
the oxygen demand, produce stable

62
00:04:25,313 --> 00:04:29,970
and predictable characteristics,
reduce odors, and allow for easy

63
00:04:30,170 --> 00:04:32,925
storage and manipulation. 

64
00:04:33,125 --> 00:04:38,157
Stabilized organic matter does not 
have an exact agreed upon scientific

65
00:04:38,357 --> 00:04:42,087
definition. But in general, it
refers to resistance to further

66
00:04:42,287 --> 00:04:47,869
biodegradation. Stabilized sludge
consists of particles like cellulose

67
00:04:48,069 --> 00:04:53,279
lignin, inorganic matter, and the 
cellular material of microorganisms

68
00:04:53,479 --> 00:04:57,844
that consume the readily degradable
organics. Whereas, unstabilized

69
00:04:58,044 --> 00:05:02,452
sludge contains easily degradable
compounds, such as carbohydrates,

70
00:05:02,652 --> 00:05:07,109
proteins, and sugars. Stabilization
can be achieved through multiple

71
00:05:07,309 --> 00:05:13,063
types of aerobic and anaerobic
treatments. For example, composting.

72
00:05:13,263 --> 00:05:17,136
Nutrient management can also be
achieved thru biological treatment.

73
00:05:17,336 --> 00:05:23,156
For example, through the 
mineralization of organic matter

74
00:05:23,356 --> 00:05:29,686
as it is degraded releasing 
nutrients into the environment.

75
00:05:29,886 --> 00:05:35,027
Or, through the immobilization of
nutrients as they are taken up 

76
00:05:35,227 --> 00:05:38,227
during growth into new cellular
material.

